div1.p:
I cannot doubt that, some time or other, the proper agents for Santa Claus will be found; and if their sphere ultimately extends also to weddings and birthdays, no matter.
It is idle to say that their services will destroy all individuality in prescnts;
there is no real individuality except in preparing every present with your own hands; and when you once buy your gifts, it makes no difference, as to the sentiment of the thing, whether you go to the shop or the shop comes to you. By all means let us have Santa Claus agencies.
